JOHANNESBURG - Authorities are urging motorists to avoid roads around the Orlando Stadium on Friday. This is due to the guard of honour that will be held for late struggle icon Winnie Madikizela-Mandela. OBITUARY: The incredible life of Winnie Madikizela-Mandela The procession will start at Sofasonke Street and continue to her home in Orlando West. "It will be from about between 11:00 and 12:00 that we know that the guard of honour will take place. From 12:00 to 13:00 we will start blocking the roads," said Wayne Minnaar, JMPD Spokesperson. "We want to advise motorists to avoid roads around the Orlando Stadium and they can use either Chris Hani or Elias Motsoaledi road as alternative routes. If they want to access the N17 they can drive through Meadowlands on Vincent road to get through on to the N17," he said. Madikazila-Mandela will be laid to rest on Saturday. eNCA